      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Nice idea from one publisher here:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.holdthefrontpage.co.uk/2020/news/magazines-devise-lockdown-challenge-to-design-front-covers/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.holdthefrontpage.co.uk/2020/news/magazines-devise-lockdown-challenge-to-design-front-covers/",
          "title": "Dalesman Publishing challenges readers to design magazine covers - Journalism News from HoldtheFrontPage",
          "description": "Budding artists and graphic designers urged to enter contest",
          "author": "Paul Linford",
          "publisher": "HoldtheFrontPage",
          "thumbnail": "https://www.holdthefrontpage.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/DalesmanMay2020-141x200.jpg",
          "icon": null
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "One of the challenges of the transition to the post-Lockdown world is maintaining and developing the enhanced relationships some publishers are developing with their readers during the crisis. But to do that, you need to find ways of helping and supporting your community through this crisis.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And many publishers are suddenly remembering that they are, at their heart, serving a community. And that involving that community is a good idea.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This is about more than consumer mags, of course.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/sofiavictoriad/status/1253814168077115393?s=21",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Local journalism has the power to make right by communities and restore the trust lost to some bad apples. Many find the idea of directly engaging with their audience a bit strange still – I cannot stress this enough, that’s where the future of journalism lies. <a href=\"https://t.co/bB03Sq14RW\">https://t.co/bB03Sq14RW</a></p>&mdash; Sofía Delgado 👩🏻‍💻 (@sofiavictoriad) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/sofiavictoriad/status/1253814168077115393?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 24, 2020</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "On a related note, I had my first ",
